                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-381" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 381 Geographic Thought and Practice (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26612" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Geography (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Geography              : An overview of the philosophy of geography and its emergence as a discipline nationally and internationally with emphasis on current concepts and their application to geographical studies in local field work analyzing the impact of human environmental interactions.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
