                <h4>Complementary Courses (27 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>27 credits selected as follows:</p>
    
      
      
                <h4>Introductory</h4>

    
              <p>12 credits of introductory courses from:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-203" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 203 Environmental Systems (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26550" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Geography (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Geography              : An introduction to system-level interactions among climate, hydrology, soils and vegetation at the scale of drainage basins, including the study of the global geographical variability in these land-surface systems. The knowledge acquired is used to study the impact on the environment of various human activities such as deforestation and urbanisation.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Timothy R Moore, Gail L Chmura (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>3 hours</li>
              <li>Restriction: Because of quantitative science content of course, not recommended for B.A. and B.Ed. students in their U0 year.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-210" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 210 Global Places and Peoples (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26554" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
